Fill my cup, fill it up and make me

00:14:37.440 --> 00:14:42.310
whole. Lord, we're thirsty; we're desperate for a fresh drink today. We're desperate to come underneath Your spout where the glory comes out. We're desperate to know more about You today; less of us and more of You. As You are the Potter, we are the clay. Mold us and make us today, Father. Create in us a clean heart. Strip off the things of this world so that the glory of the Lord rests on us today. When we stand before You, we don't stand as our own selves, but we stand underneath the blood of Jesus Christ that's washed us and made us clean. Father, we come boldly into Your throne and sit at Your feet and say, "Oh, we want to know You more."We desire to drink from Your cup. Father, I want to know the intimate things from the Word and from You, just to sit with You a while. I need You to hold me. Nothing can touch me. You are the Potter, Father. We have this treasure in earthen vessels so that the excellence of the power would be known of You and not of us. We take this time in our day just to sit at Your feet to drink from the Master's hand. Father, we need more. I know we're wall-to-wall Holy Spirit, but Father, I want to come to greater levels to soar, to come up higher where the fire's at, in the throne room, taking all this stuff off—all the stress and worries of life, the bills, the stress of work, the family drama. We just take it all and sit at Your feet and worship You today. We need refreshing, Father. Fill our cup,

